| # | Requirement                   | Classification                | Key Deciding Factor                                                                                                                                            |
| - | ----------------------------- | ----------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1 | Patient Web Portal            | **Azure Application Gateway** | Public-facing web application accessed over HTTP/HTTPS. May require SSL termination, WAF protection, and URL-based routing.                                    |
| 2 | Clinical API (Internal)       | **Azure Application Gateway** | API traffic uses HTTP/HTTPS. Can benefit from path-based routing, authentication policies, and request inspection.                                             |
| 3 | DICOM Image Streaming         | **Azure Load Balancer**       | DICOM is a medical imaging protocol that typically uses TCP, not HTTP. Requires high throughput and low latency rather than Layer 7 inspection.                |
| 4 | Auth Service (Header Routing) | **Azure Application Gateway** | Header-based routing is a Layer 7 feature. Application Gateway can inspect HTTP headers and route traffic accordingly.                                         |
| 5 | Legacy SOAP Lab Service       | **Azure Load Balancer**       | SOAP services are often exposed over TCP and usually don't need advanced Layer 7 routing. The screenshot explicitly mentions SOAP as a Load Balancer use case. |
| 6 | Admin Dashboard (Hostname)    | **Azure Application Gateway** | Hostname-based routing (e.g., admin.health.gov.in) is a key Application Gateway feature.                                                                       |
